values
  ('country', 'LB', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"apc","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.65},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.5}]'::jsonb, 'Lebanese spoken Arabic should match Levantine Arabic for everyday travel comfort. English and French are also practically useful in Lebanon.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"linguistic_reference","title":"Glottolog reference linking Lebanese Arabic to North Levantine Spoken [apc]","url":"https://glottolog.org/resource/reference/id/661333","note":"Supports mapping Lebanese spoken Arabic to the app language code apc."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Lebanon","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Lebanon","note":"Britannica describes Arabic as the official language and French and English as widely spoken."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AW', '[{"code":"pap","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"nl","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9},{"code":"es","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.75}]'::jsonb, 'Aruba should score highly for English usability in traveler reality, not just official-language baseline.', 'tourism_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Aruba.com official travel guide","url":"https://www.aruba.com/us/blog/the-official-aruba-travel-guide","note":"Official tourism copy says most Arubans also speak English and Spanish and are happy to help guests in English."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Aruba.com Papiamento page","url":"https://www.aruba.com/uk/our-island/history-and-culture/papiamento","note":"Official tourism page confirms Papiamento and Dutch as official languages."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AD', '[{"code":"ca","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"es","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9},{"code":"fr","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.7},{"code":"pt","type":"minor","coverage":0.35},{"code":"en","type":"tourist","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'Andorra should not behave like a Catalan-only destination. Spanish and French are very present; English is useful in tourism but not as universal as Spanish or French.', 'multilingual_tourism_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Andorra essential information","url":"https://visitandorra.com/en/essential-information-about-andorra/","note":"Official tourism site says Catalan is official and Spanish, French, and Portuguese are very present."},{"kind":"inference","title":"Visit Andorra English-language site","url":"https://visitandorra.com/en/","note":"English inclusion is a tourism-utility override rather than an official-language claim."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'SY', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"apc","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"minor","coverage":0.2},{"code":"fr","type":"minor","coverage":0.15}]'::jsonb, 'Syria should recognize Levantine Arabic for everyday spoken compatibility. English and French remain secondary but present, especially in urban and educated contexts.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"linguistic_reference","title":"North Levantine Arabic [apc] primary country is Syria","url":"https://dbs.org/en/research/languages/apc/","note":"Digital Bible Society language profile states North Levantine Arabic [apc] has Syria as its primary country and is spoken across the Levant."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica Students: Syria","url":"https://kids.britannica.com/students/article/Syria/277994","note":"Britannica says Arabic is the official and most widely spoken language and that English and French are also used, especially in urban areas and among the educated."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'JO', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"apc","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.55}]'::jsonb, 'Jordan should recognize Levantine Arabic for spoken compatibility, while English is broadly useful in cities and tourism.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"linguistic_reference","title":"North Levantine Arabic [apc] spoken in Jordan","url":"https://dbs.org/en/research/languages/apc/","note":"The language profile describes Levantine Arabic [apc] as spoken in Jordan as part of the Levant."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Jordan: Just the facts","url":"https://international.visitjordan.com/page/16/just-the-facts","note":"Jordan Tourism Board says Arabic is official and English is widely spoken, especially in cities."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'PS', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"apc","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"tourist","coverage":0.4}]'::jsonb, 'Palestine should treat Levantine Arabic as the practical spoken match. English is useful in many tourism and education contexts but not universal.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"linguistic_reference","title":"North Levantine Arabic [apc] spoken in Palestine","url":"https://dbs.org/en/research/languages/apc/","note":"The language profile describes Levantine Arabic [apc] as spoken in Palestine."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Travel Palestine tourism interpretation center","url":"https://www.travelpalestine.ps/en/Site/67/Tourism-Interpretation-Center","note":"Official tourism content notes documentary and visitor-facing services in Arabic and English."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'IL', '[{"code":"he","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"ar","type":"minor","coverage":0.35},{"code":"apc","type":"minor","coverage":0.3},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.85}]'::jsonb, 'Israel should score highly for English traveler usability. Hebrew dominates, while Arabic and Levantine Arabic remain important for Arab communities and some traveler interactions.', 'multilingual_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Israel","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Israel","note":"Britannica describes Hebrew as official and Arabic as having special status."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica Students: Israel","url":"https://kids.britannica.com/students/article/Israel/275101","note":"Britannica says Israeli Arabs speak a dialect of Levantine Arabic and that English is widely spoken."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AE', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.95}]'::jsonb, 'The UAE should score very highly for English traveler usability. Arabic remains official, but English is deeply embedded in everyday travel and business.', 'tourism_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Experience Abu Dhabi FAQs","url":"https://www.visitabudhabi.ae/en/faqs","note":"Official tourism site says English is widely spoken in Abu Dhabi and that most business transactions are conducted in English."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: United Arab Emirates languages and religion","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/United-Arab-Emirates/Languages-and-religion","note":"Britannica says English is widely spoken in the UAE."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'QA', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.85}]'::jsonb, 'Qatar should score highly for English traveler usability in public-facing contexts while Arabic remains official.', 'tourism_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Qatar first-time visitor guide","url":"https://visitqatar.com/intl-en/plan-your-trip/guides/first-time-visitor-guide","note":"Official tourism guidance says Arabic is official and English is commonly spoken at public places."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BH', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.85}]'::jsonb, 'Bahrain should score highly for English traveler usability, especially in tourist and commercial settings.', 'tourism_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Bahrain Tourism FAQs","url":"https://www.bahrain.com/en/faqs","note":"Official tourism FAQs say English is widely spoken, especially in hotels, restaurants, shops, and tourist areas."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"About Bahrain","url":"https://www.bahrain.com/en/about-bahrain","note":"Official tourism site says Arabic is official and English is widely spoken, with bilingual signage."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'KW', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.6}]'::jsonb, 'Kuwait should reflect strong Arabic baseline with meaningful English usability in everyday modern services and travel contexts.', 'traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Kuwait","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Kuwait/Climate","note":"Britannica says Kuwaitis speak Gulf Arabic and English is the second language taught in public schools."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Kuwait Government Online: Kuwait Finder app","url":"https://e.gov.kw/sites/kgoenglish/Pages/ApplicationPages/Application-KuwaitFinder.aspx","note":"Official app documentation highlights Arabic and English support for public navigation services."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'EG', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"arz","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.45},{"code":"fr","type":"minor","coverage":0.3}]'::jsonb, 'Egypt should match Egyptian Arabic in daily speech and give meaningful credit for English and some French among educated and tourism-facing contexts.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Languages of Egypt","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Egypt/Languages","note":"Britannica explains that Egyptians speak vernacular Egyptian Arabic and that most educated Egyptians are fluent in English or French or both."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Egypt Ministry of Tourism hotline service","url":"https://egymonuments.gov.eg/news/hot-line-service-19654/","note":"Official tourism hotline is available in Arabic and English for visitors."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'MA', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"ary","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8},{"code":"es","type":"minor","coverage":0.45},{"code":"en","type":"tourist","coverage":0.3}]'::jsonb, 'Morocco should match Moroccan Arabic and reflect the strong practical role of French and some Spanish, plus moderate English tourism usability.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Morocco language guide","url":"https://www.visitmorocco.com/en/useful-information/language","note":"Official tourism guide says Morocco''s official languages are Arabic and Amazigh, virtually all Moroccans understand French, and Spanish is widespread in northern and southern Morocco."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Tamazight language","url":"https://www.britannica.com/topic/Tamazight-language","note":"Britannica notes that French and English are also used in Morocco."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'DZ', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"arq","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.7},{"code":"en","type":"minor","coverage":0.2}]'::jsonb, 'Algeria should reflect Algerian Arabic in daily speech and the continued practical importance of French, while English remains lower-coverage.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Languages of Algeria","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Algeria/Languages","note":"Britannica says most Algerians speak vernacular Arabic and that French has long functioned as a lingua franca."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica summary: Algeria","url":"https://www.britannica.com/summary/Algeria","note":"Britannica summary lists Arabic, Tamazight, and French in common national use."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'TN', '[{"code":"ar","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"aeb","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.75},{"code":"en","type":"minor","coverage":0.3}]'::jsonb, 'Tunisia should match Tunisian Arabic in speech and reflect the major role of French, with English useful but less universal.', 'dialect_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Languages of Tunisia","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Tunisia/Languages","note":"Britannica says Arabic is official, Tunisian Arabic is the native dialect, French plays an important role, and English also serves as a lingua franca to a lesser extent."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica Students: Tunisia","url":"https://kids.britannica.com/students/article/Tunisia/277453","note":"Britannica says French is widely used in commerce and government."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BM', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Bermuda should score English as fully compatible because English is the official and practical public language for travel.', 'official_language_override', '[{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Bermuda","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Bermuda","note":"Britannica lists English as Bermuda''s official language."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Bermuda immigration English proficiency requirements","url":"https://www.gov.bm/articles/department-immigration-clarifies-english-language-proficiency-requirements","note":"Government policy uses English as the required public-language standard for immigration and work-permit purposes."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BQ', '[{"code":"nl","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8},{"code":"pap","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.65},{"code":"es","type":"minor","coverage":0.35}]'::jsonb, 'Caribbean Netherlands is an app-level aggregate of Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba. Dutch is the official administrative language, English dominates on Saba and St Eustatius, and Papiamentu is central on Bonaire.', 'aggregate_territory_language_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"CBS: Main languages of the Caribbean Netherlands","url":"https://longreads.cbs.nl/the-caribbean-netherlands-in-numbers-2022/what-percentage-of-the-population-speaks-dutch/","note":"CBS shows English as the main language on Saba and St Eustatius, while Papiamentu is the main language on Bonaire."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government.nl: Papiamento on Bonaire officially recognised","url":"https://www.government.nl/latest/news/2024/01/29/papiamento-on-bonaire-now-officially-recognised-under-the-european-charter-for-regional-and-minority-languages","note":"The Dutch government formally recognises Papiamento on Bonaire."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"InfoBonaire language guide","url":"https://infobonaire.com/about-bonaire/languages/","note":"Tourism guidance for Bonaire says Dutch is official, Papiamentu is the native majority language, and English is also widely spoken."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'CW', '[{"code":"pap","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"nl","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"es","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.65}]'::jsonb, 'Curaçao is fully multilingual for travelers: Papiamentu, Dutch, and English are official, and Spanish is also commonly usable.', 'multilingual_official_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Curaçao official tourism: native and official languages","url":"https://www.curacao.com/en/questions/culture/what-is-the-native-language-spoken-in-curacao","note":"Official tourism content says Dutch, Papiamentu, and English are official languages in Curaçao."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Curaçao official tourism: English is widely spoken","url":"https://www.curacao.com/en/questions/culture/do-people-speak-english-in-curacao","note":"Official tourism content says most Curaçaoans speak English, Dutch, Spanish, and Papiamentu."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'SX', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"nl","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.55},{"code":"es","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.4}]'::jsonb, 'Sint Maarten should not score as Dutch-only. English is official and dominant in daily life, with French and Spanish often usable in tourism-heavy settings.', 'multilingual_tourism_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit St. Maarten traveler information","url":"https://www.visitstmaarten.com/traveler-information/","note":"Official tourism guidance says Dutch is used in government on the Dutch side, English is widely spoken everywhere, and Spanish, Creole, and Papiamento are also widely spoken."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Sint Maarten policy document language profile","url":"https://www.sintmaartengov.org/Documents/Policies/Spatial%20development%20Strategy%20%2B%20attachements%20-%20Policy%20department%202022%20-%20Final.pdf","note":"Government planning material lists English and Dutch as official and shows English as the dominant public language."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'KY', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'The Cayman Islands should score English as fully compatible because English is the official public language for travelers.', 'official_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Cayman Islands official tourism FAQs","url":"https://meet.visitcaymanislands.com/en-us/services-support/faqs","note":"Official tourism FAQs state that English is the official language of the Cayman Islands."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'GI', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"es","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.75}]'::jsonb, 'Gibraltar should score English as fully compatible while also recognizing that Spanish is widely usable in everyday local conversation.', 'official_and_bilingual_usability_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Gibraltar general information","url":"https://www.visitgibraltar.gi/general-info","note":"Official tourism guidance says English is the official language and Spanish is widely spoken."},{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Gibraltar","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Gibraltar","note":"Britannica says most Gibraltarians are bilingual in English and Spanish."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BS', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"bah","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.85}]'::jsonb, 'The Bahamas should score English as fully compatible for travel. Bahamian speech includes local patois and slang, but standard English remains the practical national language for visitors. Bahamas Creole English should also count as a strong local match because it exists in the picker catalog.', 'official_language_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Constitution Commission Report: language in The Bahamas","url":"https://cdn.bahamas.gov.bs/tenant/tenanttgotb/documents/All%20Documents/ConstitutionCommissionReport20138JULY2013-20240119174548.pdf","note":"The Constitutional Commission report says English is the primary and perhaps only language of The Bahamas and recommends declaring it the national language."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Bahamas.com slang with translations","url":"https://www.bahamas.com/blog/bahamian-slang-with-translations","note":"Official tourism content explains that Bahamians code-switch between professional English and local slang, which supports English as the default traveler language."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BB', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Barbados should score English as fully compatible. Travelers may hear Bajan speech patterns, but English is the national default for public-facing travel use.', 'official_language_override', '[{"kind":"general_reference","title":"Britannica: Barbados","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Barbados","note":"Britannica lists English as Barbados''s official language."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Barbados history and culture","url":"https://www.visitbarbados.org/things-to-do/experiences/history-culture","note":"Official tourism content says Bajans speak English with a distinct local accent and vocabulary."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'JM', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Jamaica should score English as fully compatible while acknowledging the strong day-to-day presence of Jamaican Patois.', 'official_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Jamaica language guide","url":"https://www.visitjamaica.com/discover-jamaica/people-heritage/language/","note":"Official tourism content says Jamaica''s official language is English and also explains the role of Jamaican Patois."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Jamaica general information","url":"https://www.visitjamaica.com/plan-your-adventure/travel-tips/faq/","note":"Official tourism FAQs say Jamaica officially speaks English and mixes in island patois."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'TC', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"tch","type":"minor","coverage":0.35},{"code":"es","type":"minor","coverage":0.25},{"code":"fr","type":"minor","coverage":0.2}]'::jsonb, 'Turks and Caicos should score English as fully compatible. English is the official traveler-facing language, while Spanish, French, and Turks and Caicos Creole English also appear in community and everyday island use.', 'official_language_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Invest Turks and Caicos: businesses in TCI","url":"https://investturksandcaicos.tc/why-invest-in-turks-and-caicos-islands/businesses-turks-and-caicos/","note":"The official investment portal says English is the official language of the Turks and Caicos Islands, while Creole, French, and Spanish are also spoken in the expatriate community."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Invest Turks and Caicos brochure","url":"https://investturksandcaicos.tc/invest-tci-brochure/","note":"The official government brochure lists English as the language of Turks and Caicos."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'JE', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"minor","coverage":0.35}]'::jsonb, 'Jersey should score English as the practical everyday language for travelers while recognizing Jerriais as a protected heritage language and French as historically significant.', 'english_primary_with_heritage_language_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Jersey: Improve your English","url":"https://www.gov.je/lifeevents/movingtojersey/whenyouarrive/pages/improveenglish.aspx","note":"Government guidance says Jersey is predominantly English speaking, used for government services, businesses, and the majority of signs."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Jersey: Jerriais traditional language","url":"https://www.gov.je/leisure/jersey/pages/language.aspx","note":"Government guidance describes Jerriais as Jersey''s traditional language and confirms it is not widely spoken today."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'GG', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"minor","coverage":0.35}]'::jsonb, 'Guernsey should score English as the main traveler language while recognizing Guernesiais and French as culturally important but lower-coverage today.', 'english_primary_with_heritage_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Guernsey: Which languages are spoken in Guernsey?","url":"https://www.visitguernsey.com/articles/2020/which-languages-are-spoken-in-guernsey","note":"Official tourism content says English is Guernsey''s main language today and explains the heritage role of Guernesiais and historical French."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Guernsey: multilingual guide availability","url":"https://www.visitguernsey.com/experiences/activities/guided-walks/","note":"Official tourism guidance shows English by default and notes French-language guide availability."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'IM', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"gv","type":"minor","coverage":0.2}]'::jsonb, 'The Isle of Man should score English as fully usable for travelers while recognizing Manx Gaelic as a heritage language with signage and cultural visibility.', 'english_primary_with_heritage_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Isle of Man visitor guide: language","url":"https://www.isleofman.com/visitor-guide/6472/2823/get-to-know-the-isle-of-man","note":"Official visitor guidance says English is the spoken and written language of the Isle of Man, while Manx Gaelic is the traditional language."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Isle of Man visitor guide basics","url":"https://www.isleofman.com/visitor-guide","note":"Official visitor basics list the island''s language as English."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'HK', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"zh","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"yue","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Hong Kong should recognize both English and Chinese as official while acknowledging Cantonese as the dominant spoken variety in daily life.', 'official_bilingual_and_traveler_usability_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Hong Kong Tourism Board: Good to know","url":"https://www.discoverhongkong.com/us/plan/traveller-info/good-to-know.html","note":"Official tourism guidance says Chinese and English are the official languages and that Cantonese is the mother tongue of the majority of residents."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Hong Kong Official Languages Ordinance","url":"https://www.elegislation.gov.hk/hk/cap5","note":"Hong Kong law gives Chinese and English equal official status."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'MO', '[{"code":"zh","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"pt","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"yue","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.65}]'::jsonb, 'Macao should recognize Chinese and Portuguese as official while giving English meaningful credit for tourism and commerce. Cantonese is the dominant spoken Chinese variety in daily life.', 'official_multilingual_tourism_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Macao Government Tourism Office: Language","url":"https://www.macaotourism.gov.mo/en/article/about-macao/language","note":"Official tourism guidance says Chinese and Portuguese are official, Cantonese is the most widely spoken, and English is generally used in trade, tourism and commerce."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Macao SAR Government Portal tourism language note","url":"https://www.gov.mo/en/browse/tourism/","note":"The Macao SAR government portal publishes official tourism information in Chinese, Portuguese, and English."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'PR', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":0.5}]'::jsonb, 'Puerto Rico should score Spanish as the main everyday language while still giving English meaningful travel credit because it shares official status and remains common in tourism, transport, and many urban services.', 'official_bilingual_with_spanish_dominance_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Discover Puerto Rico: Essential Information","url":"https://www.discoverpuertorico.com/info/essential-information","note":"Official tourism guidance says Spanish and English are official languages and notes that Spanish is the predominant language spoken on the island."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Puerto Rico","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Puerto-Rico","note":"Britannica describes Spanish and English as official while emphasizing Spanish as the primary language of daily life."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'VI', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"es","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'The U.S. Virgin Islands should score English as the practical default for travelers while still giving Spanish partial credit because it is common in day-to-day life and visitor services.', 'english_primary_with_spanish_traveler_support_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit USVI: Travel Information","url":"https://www.visitusvi.com/travel-info","note":"Official tourism guidance presents English as the working visitor language for transport, attractions, and practical island information."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: United States Virgin Islands","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/United-States-Virgin-Islands","note":"Britannica notes English as the principal language and recognizes Spanish usage within the islands."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'VG', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"es","type":"minor","coverage":0.3}]'::jsonb, 'The British Virgin Islands should score English as fully usable for travelers while giving Spanish limited credit because it is present in the population and some service interactions, but not as the main visitor language.', 'english_primary_with_secondary_spanish_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"BVI Tourist Board: Welcome to the British Virgin Islands","url":"https://www.bvitourism.com/","note":"Official tourism materials are published for visitors in English and present English as the default practical language for travel."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: British Virgin Islands","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/British-Virgin-Islands","note":"Britannica identifies English as the official language and notes Spanish-speaking population presence."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'GU', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"ch","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.5}]'::jsonb, 'Guam should score English as the dominant traveler language while still giving Chamorro meaningful credit because it remains culturally important, visible in signage, and supported by official language institutions.', 'english_dominant_with_chamorro_visibility_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Guam Visitors Bureau: New Beach and Water Safety Signs Installed in Tumon","url":"https://www.guamvisitorsbureau.com/news/news-releases/new-beach-and-water-safety-signs-installed-in-tumon.html","note":"Official tourism guidance shows English as the default visitor language while also publishing safety information in Chamorro for residents and visitors."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Department of Chamorro Affairs","url":"https://dca.guam.gov/","note":"The official Government of Guam Department of Chamorro Affairs documents formal public support for the Chamorro language and culture."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'MP', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"ch","type":"official","coverage":0.65},{"code":"cal","type":"official","coverage":0.65}]'::jsonb, 'The Northern Mariana Islands should score English as the easiest traveler language while recognizing Chamorro and Carolinian as official and locally meaningful throughout the commonwealth.', 'official_multilingual_with_english_traveler_default_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"CNMI Constitution","url":"https://www.cnmilaw.org/cons.php","note":"The CNMI Constitution states that Chamorro, Carolinian, and English are the official languages of the commonwealth."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"The Marianas Visitors Authority","url":"https://www.mymarianas.com/","note":"Official visitor information is delivered in English while tourism branding also reflects indigenous Chamorro and Carolinian identity."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AS', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"sm","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'American Samoa should give strong credit to both English and Samoan because travelers will encounter both in government, everyday commerce, and community life across the territory.', 'bilingual_everyday_language_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"American Samoa Government Portal","url":"https://www.americansamoa.gov/","note":"The territory''s official government portal publishes practical public information in English while serving a predominantly Samoan-speaking community."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: American Samoa","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/American-Samoa","note":"Britannica describes Samoan and English as the principal languages used in American Samoa."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AI', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Anguilla should score English as fully compatible for travelers because government and visitor-facing information consistently treat it as the island''s practical language.', 'official_english_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Anguilla: Anguilla Facts","url":"https://www.gov.ai/service/anguilla-facts","note":"The Government of Anguilla facts page lists English as the island''s language."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Anguilla","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Anguilla-island-West-Indies","note":"Britannica identifies English as Anguilla''s official language."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BZ', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"bzj","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8},{"code":"es","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.4}]'::jsonb, 'Belize should score English as fully usable for travelers while also giving strong credit to Belize Kriol, which is spoken widely in daily life across the country.', 'official_english_with_kriol_daily_use_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Travel Belize: Facts About Belize","url":"https://www.travelbelize.org/es/facts-about-belize","note":"Official tourism guidance says English is Belize''s official language and that Belizeans also speak Kriol and Spanish."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Travel Belize: Know Before You Go | 8 Kriol Phrases","url":"https://www.travelbelize.org/blog/know-you-go-8-kriol-phrases/","note":"Official tourism content says Kriol is widely and proudly spoken throughout Belize."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'CV', '[{"code":"pt","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"kea","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Cabo Verde should recognize Portuguese as the official language while giving equally strong practical credit to Kabuverdianu, the mother tongue and everyday language of most residents.', 'official_portuguese_with_kabuverdianu_majority_use_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Cabo Verde: Língua Portuguesa","url":"https://www.governo.cv/lancamento-das-olimpiadas-de-lingua-portuguesa/","note":"Government education policy references Portuguese as the language of formal schooling and public instruction."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Cabo Verde: Língua e Cultura Cabo-verdiana","url":"https://www.governo.cv/ministerio-da-educacao-decide-suspender-distribuicao-do-manual-de-lingua-e-cultura-cabo-verdiana-do-10o-ano/","note":"Government education guidance explicitly treats Cabo-verdian language and culture as a distinct language domain in the school system."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Digital Bible Society: Kabuverdianu [kea]","url":"https://dbs.org/es/research/languages/kea/","note":"DBS identifies Kabuverdianu as the primary creole language of Cabo Verde and the native language of virtually all Cape Verdeans."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'DM', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Dominica should score English as the main traveler language. Kwéyòl is important locally, but it does not yet have a clean exact-code match in the app''s picker catalog, so it will be handled in the final reconciliation pass.', 'official_english_with_local_creole_note_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Discover Dominica: Useful Information","url":"https://discoverdominica.com/en/useful-information","note":"Official tourism guidance says English is the official language of Dominica and notes that a large portion of the population also speaks Kwéyòl."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Division of Culture Dominica: Kwéyòl","url":"https://divisionofculture.gov.dm/creole-languages/5-kweyol","note":"Dominica''s culture division documents Kwéyòl as a real living language on the island, which supports a future exact-code reconciliation pass."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'DO', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.65}]'::jsonb, 'The Dominican Republic should score Spanish as the dominant traveler language while also giving meaningful English credit because it is widely used in tourist areas, hotels, and guided experiences.', 'official_spanish_with_tourist_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Dominican Republic Tourism: Travel Tips","url":"https://www.godominicanrepublic.com/en/travel/travel-tips","note":"Official tourism guidance says Spanish is the official language and that English is widely spoken in tourist areas."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Dominican Republic Tourism: FAQs","url":"https://www.godominicanrepublic.com/en/travel/faqs","note":"Official tourism FAQs say visitors who do not speak Spanish can still communicate in big cities and most tourist destinations because hotel, restaurant, and tour staff speak English."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'GP', '[{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"gcf","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8}]'::jsonb, 'Guadeloupe should recognize French as the official language while also giving strong local credit to Guadeloupean Creole French, which remains widely spoken in daily life and cultural expression.', 'official_french_with_local_creole_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Guadeloupe Islands: Gwo-Ka","url":"https://www.guadeloupe-islands.com/gwo-ka/","note":"Official tourism content describes Guadeloupean Creole as the language used in core local music and cultural performance."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Guadeloupe","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Guadeloupe/People","note":"Britannica says French is the official language of Guadeloupe and that a local creole is also widely spoken."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'MQ', '[{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Martinique should score French as fully usable for travelers. Martinican Creole is spoken widely in local life, but it does not yet map cleanly to an exact picker code in the current app catalog, so it will be included in the final reconciliation pass.', 'official_french_with_creole_everyday_use_note_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Martinique Tourisme: Martinican Creole","url":"https://www.martinique.org/en/about/culture/creole","note":"Official tourism guidance says French is the official language and explains that Martinican Creole is spoken everywhere and by everyone in day-to-day life."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Martinique Tourisme: Culture","url":"https://www.martinique.org/en/about/culture","note":"Official tourism content says French is official and that Creole is the language often used in family, community, and cultural settings."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'RE', '[{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"rcf","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8}]'::jsonb, 'Réunion should recognize French as official while giving strong practical credit to Réunion Creole French, which is spoken widely across the island and appears throughout local tourism and cultural life.', 'official_french_with_reunion_creole_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Île de la Réunion Tourisme: Creole Glossary","url":"https://en.reunion.fr/organize/useful-information-before-travelling/creole-glossary/","note":"Official tourism guidance says French is the official language on Réunion and that the population also speaks Creole."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Réunion","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Reunion","note":"Britannica lists French as the official language and says Réunion French Creole is the language in common use."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'YT', '[{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"swb","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9},{"code":"buc","type":"minor","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'Mayotte should score French as the official administrative language while also giving strong everyday credit to Maore Comorian and some credit to Bushi, both of which remain important in daily communication across the island.', 'official_french_with_indigenous_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"France.fr: Mayotte","url":"https://www.france.fr/en/destination/mayotte/","note":"Official tourism guidance says French is the official language and explains that Shimaore dominates conversations in most regions while Kibushi remains important in parts of the island."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Mayotte","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Mayotte","note":"Britannica lists French as the official language and says most of the people speak Comorian while some villages use a Malagasy dialect."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Digital Bible Society: Maore Comorian [swb]","url":"https://dbs.org/en/research/languages/swb/","note":"DBS identifies Maore Comorian as the primary indigenous language of Mayotte and ties it directly to the territory code YT."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'GD', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Grenada should score English as fully usable for travelers. Local French-African patois remains culturally present, but it does not yet map cleanly to an exact picker code in the current app catalog and will be handled in the final reconciliation pass.', 'official_english_with_local_patois_note_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Grenada Tourism Authority FAQs","url":"https://www.puregrenada.com/faqs/","note":"Official tourism guidance says English is the official language in Grenada and notes that locals may also speak French-African patois."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Grenada","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Grenada-island-West-Indies","note":"Britannica lists English as the official language of Grenada."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'KN', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'St. Kitts and Nevis should score English as fully compatible for travelers because official tourism guidance treats it as the primary language for visitor services and communication.', 'official_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"St. Kitts Tourism Authority FAQ","url":"https://www.visitstkitts.com/plan/faq","note":"Official tourism FAQs say the primary language of St. Kitts is English."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Saint Kitts and Nevis","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Saint-Kitts-and-Nevis","note":"Britannica identifies English as the official language of Saint Kitts and Nevis."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'LC', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"acf","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8}]'::jsonb, 'Saint Lucia should recognize English as the official language while also giving strong credit to Saint Lucian Creole French, which the government explicitly treats as a living national language in schools and cultural life.', 'official_english_with_kweyol_daily_use_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Saint Lucia: Kwéyòl classes in Saint Lucian schools begin this September","url":"https://www.govt.lc/news/kw-y-l-classes-in-saint-lucian-schools-begin-this-september","note":"The Government of Saint Lucia describes Kwéyòl as a core part of Saint Lucian identity and confirms it is being introduced into schools as a living language."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Saint Lucia Ministry of Tourism: National Language Policy underway","url":"https://tourism.govt.lc/news/national-language-policy-underway-for-saint-lucia","note":"Saint Lucia''s tourism ministry language-policy article says Kwéyòl is a home language for many students and discusses bilingual goals in English and Kwéyòl."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'TT', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Trinidad and Tobago should score English as fully compatible for travelers. The country also has a strong local creole/dialect continuum, but the exact-code reconciliation for that speech variety will be handled in the final cleanup pass.', 'official_english_with_local_dialect_note_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Trinidad: Travel Tips","url":"https://visittrinidad.tt/plan-your-trip/travel-tips/","note":"Official tourism guidance says English is the official language of Trinidad while also noting the informal use of a creative local dialect."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Trinidad and Tobago","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Trinidad-and-Tobago","note":"Britannica lists English as the official language of Trinidad and Tobago."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'VC', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'St. Vincent and the Grenadines should score English as fully compatible for travelers because official tourism guidance presents English as the island nation''s practical language for visitors.', 'official_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Discover SVG: Bequia","url":"https://discoversvg.com/island/bequia/","note":"Official tourism guidance for St. Vincent and the Grenadines says the official language is English."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Saint Vincent and the Grenadines","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Saint-Vincent-and-the-Grenadines","note":"Britannica identifies English as the official language of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BL', '[{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8}]'::jsonb, 'Saint Barthélemy should recognize French as official while giving strong credit to English because official tourism services are consistently bilingual and English is widely usable in the island''s visitor economy.', 'official_french_with_high_english_tourism_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Saint Barth Tourism Office","url":"https://www.saintbarth-tourisme.com/localisation-office-de-tourisme/","note":"The official tourism office operates a bilingual French/English visitor site, supporting strong traveler usability in English."},{"kind":"secondary_reference","title":"Petit Futé: Saint-Barthélemy population and languages","url":"https://www.petitfute.co.uk/p221-saint-barthelemy/decouvrir/d470-population/","note":"This travel reference says French is the official language of Saint Barthélemy and that English is widely spoken."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'MF', '[{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.85}]'::jsonb, 'The French side of Saint-Martin should score French as official while giving equally strong practical credit to English because public-facing institutions and the tourism economy operate comfortably in both.', 'official_french_with_widely_spoken_english_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Collectivité de Saint-Martin English pages","url":"https://www.comstmartin.fr/en/alertes/impot-sur-le-revenu-2024--date-limite-de-declaration-reportee-au-20-juin-2025","note":"The Collectivité publishes official public information in both French and English, which supports strong functional English usability."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Saint Martin","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Saint-Martin-island-West-Indies","note":"Britannica says French is the official language on the French side of the island and that English is widely spoken."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'MS', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Montserrat should score English as fully compatible for travelers. A local English-lexifier creole is also spoken, but exact-code reconciliation for that variety will be handled in the final cleanup pass.', 'official_english_with_local_creole_note_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Montserrat: Contact Us","url":"https://blog.visitmontserrat.com/contact-us/","note":"Montserrat''s official tourism organization presents visitor services entirely in English, supporting English as the practical travel language."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Montserrat","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Montserrat-island-West-Indies","note":"Britannica says the official language is English, while also noting that most Montserratians speak a Creole language."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'SR', '[{"code":"nl","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"srn","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9},{"code":"en","type":"minor","coverage":0.35}]'::jsonb, 'Suriname should recognize Dutch as the official language while giving very strong practical credit to Sranan Tongo, the country''s common lingua franca. English also deserves modest credit because official travel guidance says most Surinamese speak basic English.', 'official_dutch_with_sranan_lingua_franca_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Suriname Travel: Facts About Suriname","url":"https://suriname.travel/facts-about-suriname/","note":"Official tourism guidance says Dutch is the official language, Sranan Tongo is the common language, and most Surinamese speak basic English."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Permanent Mission of Suriname to the United Nations: Country Facts","url":"https://www.un.int/suriname/suriname/country-facts","note":"Suriname''s UN mission lists Dutch as official, English as widely spoken in Paramaribo, and Sranan Tongo as a national creole language."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Digital Bible Society: Sranan Tongo [srn]","url":"https://dbs.org/en/research/languages/srn/","note":"DBS identifies Sranan Tongo as Suriname''s unofficial national language and lingua franca."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'HT', '[{"code":"ht","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'Haiti should give full credit to Haitian Creole in everyday compatibility and meaningful secondary credit to French, which remains an official language used more in formal and institutional contexts.', 'official_haitian_with_french_formal_use_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Haiti: Haitian Creole words and expressions","url":"https://visithaiti.com/fr/haiti-de-pres/mots-et-expressions-en-creole-haitien/","note":"Official tourism content actively teaches Haitian Creole to visitors, which supports its role as the primary everyday travel language."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Haiti","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Haiti/Climate","note":"Britannica says Haitian Creole and French are both official, with Creole used in daily life and French used more in formal circumstances."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'CR', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.7}]'::jsonb, 'Costa Rica should score Spanish as the official and dominant language while also giving strong English credit because official travel guidance says many Costa Ricans speak English well, especially across the tourism economy.', 'official_spanish_with_high_tourism_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Costa Rica: Tips","url":"https://www.visitcostarica.com/planning-your-trip/tips","note":"Official tourism guidance says the native tongue is Spanish and that many Costa Ricans speak English quite well."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Costa Rica languages","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Costa-Rica/Languages","note":"Britannica identifies Spanish as the national language and also notes English-based creole speech in Limón."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'CU', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.6}]'::jsonb, 'Cuba should score Spanish as fully dominant while giving meaningful English credit because official tourism guidance says a good part of the population speaks English and the tourist sector frequently does so.', 'official_spanish_with_tourism_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Cuba Travel: Society","url":"https://www.cuba.travel/en/","note":"Official tourism guidance says the official language in Cuba is Spanish and that a good part of the population also speaks English, especially in the tourist sector."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Cuba Travel: Tourist Information Centers","url":"https://www.cuba.travel/en/useful-information/tourist-information-centers-in-cuba/1000","note":"Official tourism information centers say they provide assistance in several languages for travelers."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'HN', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"minor","coverage":0.2}]'::jsonb, 'Honduras should score Spanish as the dominant traveler language. English gets only limited credit because official travel guidance regularly warns that many local guides and offices work primarily in Spanish outside the most tourist-oriented areas.', 'official_spanish_with_limited_tourism_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Honduras Travel: Talgua Caves","url":"https://hondurastravel.com/honduras-destinations/olancho/the-talgua-caves/","note":"Official tourism guidance says local guides there do not speak English and recommends Spanish to enjoy the visit fully."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Honduras Travel: Cuero y Salado Wildlife Refuge","url":"https://hondurastravel.com/national-parks/overnight-at-the-cuero-y-salado-wildlife-refuge-facilities/","note":"Official tourism guidance says it is best if travelers speak Spanish because English-speaking help is not always available."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'NI', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"minor","coverage":0.3}]'::jsonb, 'Nicaragua should score Spanish as the dominant national language while giving modest English credit because official tourism guidance says English is used along parts of the Caribbean coast.', 'official_spanish_with_caribbean_english_use_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Nicaragua: Fast Facts","url":"https://visitnicaragua.us/about-nicaragua/fast-facts/","note":"Official tourism guidance says Spanish is the official language and that English and indigenous languages are used along the Caribbean coast and Atlantic plain."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Nicaragua: Languages of Nicaragua''s Caribbean Coast","url":"https://visitnicaragua.us/2022/02/languages-of-nicaraguas-caribbean-coast/","note":"Official tourism guidance explains the multilingual Caribbean coast and supports giving English some regional but not nationwide credit."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'SV', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'El Salvador should score Spanish as the clear traveler language. Nahuat remains locally meaningful in some communities, but exact-code reconciliation for that language will be handled in the final cleanup pass.', 'official_spanish_with_indigenous_language_note_override', '[{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: El Salvador","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/El-Salvador","note":"Britannica identifies Spanish as the official language of El Salvador."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"El Salvador Travel: Cascadas El Escuco","url":"https://elsalvador.travel/esp/en/destination/cascadas-el-escuco/","note":"Official tourism guidance notes that Nahuat is still spoken in some local communities, which supports a later indigenous-language reconciliation pass."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AR', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'Argentina should score Spanish as the clear national language while giving moderate English credit because the official tourism platform serves international travelers directly in English and other languages, even though everyday use remains overwhelmingly Spanish.', 'official_spanish_with_tourism_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Argentina English site","url":"https://www.argentina.travel/en","note":"Argentina''s official tourism platform serves international trip-planning content in English, supporting real English usability in the tourism sector."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Argentina","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Argentina","note":"Britannica identifies Spanish as the national language of Argentina."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BR', '[{"code":"pt","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.45},{"code":"es","type":"minor","coverage":0.35}]'::jsonb, 'Brazil should recognize Portuguese as the official language while giving moderate credit to English and some credit to Spanish because official tourism guidance says both are spoken in many tourist areas and large cities.', 'official_portuguese_with_tourism_english_and_spanish_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Brasil: Idioma","url":"https://visitbrasil.com/pt/home/about-brazil/lingua/","note":"Official tourism guidance says Portuguese is the official language and that many people in tourist areas and large cities also speak English and Spanish."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Brazil","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Brazil","note":"Britannica identifies Portuguese as the official language of Brazil."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'CL', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.4}]'::jsonb, 'Chile should score Spanish as dominant while giving moderate English credit because the official tourism platform and visitor assistance infrastructure are deliberately multilingual, even though everyday national use is primarily Spanish.', 'official_spanish_with_multilingual_tourism_support_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Chile Travel multilingual visitor platform","url":"https://chile.travel/en/","note":"Chile''s official tourism portal is served in English, Spanish, Portuguese, and German, supporting meaningful English usability for trip planning and visitor support."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Chile","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Chile","note":"Britannica identifies Spanish as the dominant language of Chile."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'PY', '[{"code":"es","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"gn","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Paraguay should give full credit to both Spanish and Guaraní because both are official and Guaraní is unusually strong as an everyday national language, not just a heritage language.', 'coofficial_spanish_and_guarani_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Paraguay: El Festival del País","url":"https://visitparaguay.travel/events/el-festival-del-pais","note":"Paraguay''s official tourism platform actively publishes cultural content in both castellano and guaraní, reflecting Guaraní''s living national status."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Paraguay","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Paraguay","note":"Britannica states that Spanish and Guaraní are Paraguay''s official languages and that Guaraní is more widely spoken than Spanish."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AT', '[{"code":"de","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.7}]'::jsonb, 'Austria should score German as the official language while giving strong English credit because the national tourism board says English is widely understood and spoken fluently by most people working in tourism.', 'official_german_with_high_tourism_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Austria Tourism: A-Z of Austria","url":"https://b2b.austria.info/uk/about-austria/a-z-of-austria/","note":"Austria''s national tourism board says German is spoken by most of the population and that English is widely understood and spoken fluently by most people working within the tourism industry."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Austria Tourism: The Basics","url":"https://b2b.austria.info/us/about-austria/fast-facts/the-basics/","note":"Austria''s tourism board identifies Austrian German as the language spoken in Austria."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'CH', '[{"code":"de","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"it","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"rm","type":"official","coverage":0.3}]'::jsonb, 'Switzerland should give full credit to German, French, and Italian as major national languages, plus partial credit to Romansh in the regions where it is used. This is country-level, so city and canton differences will matter later.', 'multiofficial_language_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Switzerland Tourism: Language distribution","url":"https://www.myswitzerland.com/en-au/planning/about-switzerland/general-facts/facts-about-switzerland/language-distribution/","note":"Switzerland Tourism explains the country''s four languages and gives national distribution figures for German, French, Italian, and Romansh."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Switzerland Tourism: private group tours at ETH Zurich","url":"https://www.myswitzerland.com/en-us/experiences/private-group-tours-at-eth-zurich/","note":"Official tourism listings regularly show multilingual visitor services, including German, French, Italian, and English."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'DK', '[{"code":"da","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9}]'::jsonb, 'Denmark should score Danish as the national language while giving very high English credit because VisitDenmark explicitly says it is easy to get around in English and that over 90% of Danes speak it fluently.', 'official_danish_with_very_high_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"VisitDenmark: Language","url":"https://www.visitdenmark.com/faq/language","note":"VisitDenmark says the national language is Danish."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"VisitDenmark: Speaking English in Denmark","url":"https://www.visitdenmark.com/faq/speaking-english-in-denmark","note":"VisitDenmark says Danes have a very good level of English and that it is easy to get around the country even if you do not speak Danish."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"VisitDenmark: Denmark basics for event planners","url":"https://www.visitdenmark.com/business-events/contacts/denmark-basics","note":"VisitDenmark says over 90% of Danes speak English fluently."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BE', '[{"code":"nl","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"de","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.6}]'::jsonb, 'Belgium should give full credit to Dutch, French, and German as official languages while also giving meaningful English credit because Belgian government travel guidance says English is frequently spoken.', 'multiofficial_language_with_common_english_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"FPS Foreign Affairs: Country facts","url":"https://taipei.diplomatie.belgium.be/en/travel-belgium/country-facts","note":"Belgian foreign affairs guidance says Dutch, French, and German are the official languages and that English is frequently spoken."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"FPS Health: Languages in Belgium","url":"https://www.health.belgium.be/sites/default/files/uploads/fields/fpshealth_theme_file/01_spain_icd10be_eng_20140530_0.pdf","note":"Belgian federal documentation describes the country''s Dutch-, French-, and German-speaking communities."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'CA', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Canada should give full credit to both English and French because they are the country''s two official languages and are institutionally supported nationwide, even though city and province differences will matter later.', 'coofficial_english_and_french_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Canada.ca: Official Languages Day","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/canadian-heritage/campaigns/official-languages-day.html","note":"Government of Canada guidance says French and English are Canada''s two official languages."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Canada.ca: Official Languages Act and you","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/treasury-board-secretariat/services/values-ethics/official-languages/official-languages-act-and-you.html","note":"Government guidance explains that English and French are Canada''s official languages and have equal status in federal institutions."}]'::jsonb),
