  ('country', 'DE', '[{"code":"de","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.7}]'::jsonb, 'Germany should score German as the official language while giving strong English credit because the national tourism board explicitly says a large proportion of the population speaks English and that language barriers should not pose a problem for many visitors.', 'official_german_with_high_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Germany Travel: Information on Germany","url":"https://www.germany.travel/en/information-on-germany.html","note":"Germany''s national tourism board says the official language is German and that a large proportion of the population also speaks English, so language barriers should not pose a problem for many international visitors."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Germany","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Germany","note":"Britannica identifies German as the official language of Germany."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'NL', '[{"code":"nl","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9}]'::jsonb, 'The Netherlands should score Dutch as the national language while giving very high English credit because official visitor guidance says English is widely spoken throughout the country and around 90% of the population speaks it.', 'official_dutch_with_very_high_english_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of the Netherlands: Civic integration","url":"https://www.government.nl/topics/integration-in-the-netherlands/civic-integration-in-the-netherlands","note":"Government guidance treats Dutch as the standard language newcomers are expected to learn, supporting Dutch as the national default language."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"I amsterdam: Visitor information","url":"https://www.iamsterdam.com/en/travel-stay/visitor-information","note":"Official visitor guidance says English is widely spoken in Amsterdam and throughout the Netherlands, with approximately 90% of the population speaking it."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'NO', '[{"code":"no","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8}]'::jsonb, 'Norway should score Norwegian as the national language while giving strong English credit because official travel guidance says most Norwegians speak English.', 'official_norwegian_with_high_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Norway: Travel tips A-Z","url":"https://www.visitnorway.com/plan-your-trip/travel-tips-a-z/","note":"Visit Norway says most Norwegians speak English, especially younger people."},{"kind":"reference","title":"Britannica: Norway","url":"https://www.britannica.com/place/Norway","note":"Britannica identifies Norwegian as the principal language of Norway."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'FI', '[{"code":"fi","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"sv","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8}]'::jsonb, 'Finland should give full credit to Finnish and Swedish as official languages while also giving strong English credit because government guidance says English is widely spoken and tourism guidance says travelers can get around in English almost everywhere.', 'coofficial_finnish_and_swedish_with_high_english_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"This is FINLAND: A guide to Finnish customs and manners","url":"https://finland.fi/life-society/a-guide-to-finnish-customs-and-manners/","note":"Government-backed Finland guidance says English is widely spoken in Finland and explains the co-official roles of Finnish and Swedish."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Finland: Discover Helsinki","url":"https://www.visitfinland.com/en/places-to-go/helsinki-region/helsinki-city/","note":"Official tourism guidance says Finnish and Swedish are Finland''s official languages and that travelers can get around speaking English almost everywhere."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'IE', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"ga","type":"official","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'Ireland should give full credit to English and Irish because both are official, while English remains the primary language travelers will use almost everywhere and Irish stays especially strong in Gaeltacht regions.', 'coofficial_english_and_irish_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Ireland.com: Languages of Ireland","url":"https://www.ireland.com/en/a-sites/help-and-advice/practical-information/languages-of-ireland/","note":"Official tourism guidance says English and Irish are the official languages in the Republic of Ireland, that everyone speaks English, and that Irish is widely spoken in Gaeltacht areas."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Ireland.com language facts","url":"https://www.ireland.com/en-se/help-and-advice/practical-information/languages-of-ireland/","note":"A second official tourism variant repeats that English is primary while Irish remains a living local language in designated regions."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'IS', '[{"code":"is","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.9}]'::jsonb, 'Iceland should score Icelandic as the official language while giving very high English credit because government guidance says it is hard to find an Icelander who does not speak English and that English is spoken fluently and widely.', 'official_icelandic_with_very_high_english_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Work in Iceland: Icelandic society","url":"https://work.iceland.is/living/icelandic-society/","note":"Government relocation guidance says Icelandic is the official language and that it would be hard to find an Icelander who does not speak English."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Study in Iceland: Learning Icelandic","url":"https://study.iceland.is/practical-guide/learning-icelandic","note":"Government-backed study guidance says English is spoken fluently and widely in Iceland."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'LU', '[{"code":"lb","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"de","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.7}]'::jsonb, 'Luxembourg should recognize Luxembourgish, French, and German while also giving strong English credit because official tourism guidance says English is among the other languages widely spoken across the country.', 'multiofficial_language_with_high_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Luxembourg: Practical information","url":"https://www.visitluxembourg.com/plan-your-stay/practical-information","note":"Official tourism guidance says Luxembourgish is the national language, French and German are official languages, and English is among the other languages widely spoken."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Luxembourg: Wiltz","url":"https://www.visitluxembourg.com/wiltz","note":"Official visitor information says tourists are welcomed in German, French, Luxembourgish, English, and Dutch."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'AU', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Australia should score English as fully compatible for travelers. Indigenous languages remain culturally important across the country, but exact-code regional assignment for them belongs in the later city and reconciliation passes rather than a country-level override.', 'english_primary_with_indigenous_language_note_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Australia.com: Facts about Australia","url":"https://www.australia.com/en/facts-and-planning/facts-about-australia.html","note":"Australia''s official tourism guidance says the national language is English and describes the country''s multicultural setting."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Australia.gov.au: About Australia","url":"https://www.australia.gov.au/about-australia","note":"Government of Australia guidance describes English as the national language used across the country."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'NZ', '[{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1},{"code":"mi","type":"official","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'New Zealand should give full credit to English as the primary everyday language for travelers while also giving meaningful credit to Māori because it is an official language and visible in public life, culture, and signage.', 'english_primary_with_maori_official_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"100% Pure New Zealand: About New Zealand","url":"https://www.newzealand.com/int/feature/new-zealand-travel-guide/","note":"Official tourism guidance says the primary language is English and highlights Māori as part of New Zealand''s core identity and visitor experience."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"NZHistory: Māori Language Act 1987","url":"https://nzhistory.govt.nz/culture/maori-language-week/history-of-the-maori-language","note":"New Zealand government history guidance explains that Māori became an official language in 1987."}]'::jsonb),
