  ('country', 'MU', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"fr","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.8},{"code":"mfe","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Mauritius should score English as the official administrative language while also giving strong practical credit to French and Mauritian Creole, both of which are deeply embedded in everyday island life and tourism.', 'english_official_with_french_and_creole_everyday_use_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Visit Mauritius: Language","url":"https://app-staging.visitmauritius.com/mauritius","note":"Official Mauritius tourism guidance says English serves government, administration, education, and business; French has a strong presence; and the majority of the population speaks Mauritian Creole."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Mauritius Now: Explore the Languages Spoken in Mauritius","url":"https://mauritiusnow.com/blog/things-to-do/mauritius-language-learn-some-creole/","note":"Official destination-marketing guidance says English, French, and Mauritian Creole are the three languages widely spoken on the island."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'GY', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Guyana should score English as the official national language while recognizing that Creolese and Indigenous languages matter in daily life. English is still the safest country-level traveler language by far.', 'official_english_with_creolese_note_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Guyana Tourism FAQ","url":"https://guyanatourism.com/faq/","note":"Official tourism guidance says English is Guyana''s official first language and notes that Creolese and several Indigenous dialects are also spoken."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Guyana Tourism multilingual site","url":"https://guyanatourism.com/plan-your-trip/","note":"Guyana''s tourism authority serves international visitors through a multilingual planning platform while treating English as the primary working language."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'NA', '[{"code":"en","type":"official","coverage":1}]'::jsonb, 'Namibia should score English as the official language while acknowledging that many people use other local and regional languages in daily life. For country-level travel compatibility, English remains the cleanest default.', 'official_english_with_multilingual_daily_use_override', '[{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Government of Namibia: About Namibia","url":"https://www.gov.na/aboutnamibia","note":"The Government of Namibia lists English as the official language."},{"kind":"government_reference","title":"Constitution of the Republic of Namibia","url":"https://kavangowestrc.gov.na/documents/2330712/2721183/Constitution%2Bof%2Bthe%2BRepublic%2Bof%2BNamibia.pdf/b92c72f3-712c-2795-1cfd-6e00f925a9ec?t=1692880681519","note":"Article 3 of the Namibian Constitution states that the official language of Namibia is English."}]'::jsonb),
  ('country', 'BG', '[{"code":"bg","type":"official","coverage":1},{"code":"en","type":"widely_spoken","coverage":0.45}]'::jsonb, 'Bulgaria should score Bulgarian as the official language while giving moderate English credit because official tourism guidance consistently shows visitor centers, museums, and guides serving travelers in English.', 'official_bulgarian_with_tourism_english_override', '[{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Bulgaria Travel: Ruse tourist information center","url":"https://visitbulgaria.com/city-of-ruse/","note":"Official tourism guidance says tourists in the Ruse Tourist Information Center are attended by guides in Bulgarian and English."},{"kind":"official_tourism","title":"Bulgaria Travel: Rila Monastery visitor services","url":"https://visitbulgaria.com/natural-park-rila-monastery/","note":"Official tourism guidance says guided tours in key visitor sites are offered in Bulgarian and English."}]'::jsonb),
